              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Use keyword research tools like Ahrefs or Semrush filtered by low keyword difficulty, check Google Autocomplete and People Also Ask boxes, explore Reddit and Quora for natural language, and review Google Search Console performance data for queries already driving impressions in positions 5-20.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Can one page rank for multiple long-tail keywords?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Absolutely. Comprehensive, thorough pages regularly rank for dozens or hundreds of related variations through semantic relationships. Google's natural language understanding matches a page to queries that share intent and meaning, not just exact keyword matches.</p></div></div>
